matplotlib.rcParams['font.family'] = 'sans-serif'
#  
def show_distribution(column, title, ylim=[0, 50], number_of_bins=15, range_of_values=(0, 10)):
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))
    ax1 = fig.add_subplot(1, 2, 1)
    ax2 = fig.add_subplot(1, 2, 2)
    #    
    ax2.yaxis.set_minor_locator(AutoMinorLocator())
    ax2.tick_params(which='minor', length=2, width=1)
    #     
    ax1.spines['bottom'].set_visible(False)
    ax2.spines['top'].set_visible(False)
    ax2.spines['right'].set_visible(False)
    ax1.xaxis.set_visible(False)
    #   
    
    fig.suptitle(f'    : {title}', fontsize=14)
    #  
    flats_df.boxplot(
                           column, 
                           ax=ax1,
                           widths=0.4,
                           showmeans=True, 
                           meanline=True, 
                           color='#1E2022', 
                           flierprops=dict(marker='D', markerfacecolor='white', markeredgecolor='#0D3472', linewidth=1.5),
                           medianprops=dict(linewidth=1.5, color='maroon'),
                           boxprops=dict(linewidth=1.2, color='#1E2022'),
                           meanprops=dict(linewidth=1.5, color='#E32A20')
                          ).set_ylim(ylim)
    flats_df.hist(column, ax=ax2, bins=number_of_bins, range=range_of_values, color='#4A75A5')
    #     
    ax2.set_title(None)
    
    fig.tight_layout()
    return plt.show()

def get_floor_category(row):
    try:
        if row['floor'] == row['floors_total']:
            return ''
        if row['floor'] == 1:
            return ''
        else:
            return ''
    except:
        return np.nan

def plot_hist(column, column_name, x_range=(0, 200), number_of_bins=25):
    fig_total_area = plt.figure(figsize=(9,5))
    ax1 = fig_total_area.add_subplot(1,1,1)
    ax1.grid(which='major', linewidth=1, color='gray', alpha=0.2)
    ax1.set_title(f' : {column_name}', fontsize=14)
    sns.histplot(x=column, data=flats_df, ax=ax1, color='#0D3578', bins=number_of_bins).set(xlim=x_range)

    plt.show()
#
